               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18150111-122-person1031">
                  MARGARET
                  MADDISON
               <interp inst="t18150111-122-person1031" type="surname" value="MADDISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150111-122-person1031" type="given" value="MARGARET"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150111-122-person1031" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My husband's name is 
               <persName id="t18150111-122-person1032">
                  William
                  Maddison
               <interp inst="t18150111-122-person1032" type="surname" value="Maddison"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150111-122-person1032" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150111-122-person1032" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I lost my table spoons out of my yard. The prisoner is a <rs id="t18150111-122-deflabel698" type="occupation">dust boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18150111-122-defend1028 t18150111-122-deflabel698"></join>; he came in my yard on the 22nd of December, to take my dust away; I opened the door to let him in; I had made use of the spoon about half an hour before the boy took it away. It was in a saucepan that stood in the yard. I missed the spoon between nine and ten in the morning; I saw my spoon again on the 8th of January.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18150111-122-person1033">
                  SAMUEL
                  ROUS
               <interp inst="t18150111-122-person1033" type="surname" value="ROUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150111-122-person1033" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150111-122-person1033" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I apprehended the prisoner. I took him for stealing a spoon out of Mrs. Maddison's saucepan in the yard; he said, he did take it, and his mother sold the spoon. This is the spoon.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18150111-122-person1034">
                  JOHN
                  MORRIS
               <interp inst="t18150111-122-person1034" type="surname" value="MORRIS"></interp>
